wiki.summary: In “In My Head,” while Lil Tjay samples Iyaz’s 2009 viral hit, “Replay,” he also raps about his emotions for a specific lady, heavily contrasting to the compared hit, “Calling My Phone.” Lil Tjay first previewed the song in a Tweet where he displayed a music video shoot with lyrics from the chorus playing in the back. On March 10, Tjay officially posted a snippet on his TikTok page where he had named it as the “Best sample of the year?👀” Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: In “In My Head,” while Lil Tjay samples Iyaz’s 2009 viral hit, “Replay,” he also raps about his emotions for a specific lady, heavily contrasting to the compared hit, “Calling My Phone.” Lil Tjay first previewed the song in a Tweet where he displayed a music video shoot with lyrics from the chorus playing in the back. On March 10, Tjay officially posted a snippet on his TikTok page where he had named it as the “Best sample of the year?👀” “In My Head” debuted and peaked at #33 on the Billboard Hot 100 for the chart week ending April 16, 2022.
